RETIREMENT NOTICE

Legacy authentication protocol removal for Exchange Online

Microsoft is retiring support for legacy authentication protocols in Exchange Online as part of our ongoing security improvements.

Admin impact: Organizations still using legacy authentication methods will need to migrate to modern authentication.

What you need to know:
- Basic authentication will be permanently disabled
- OAuth 2.0 is the recommended authentication method
- All mailbox access protocols are affected (POP, IMAP, SMTP)

Affected services:
- Exchange Online

This change will help protect your organization from security threats associated with legacy authentication methods.

No immediate action required, but we recommend planning your migration to modern authentication soon.

For technical details and migration guidance, see the Message Center documentation.
